(firstQuint)Balanced Solution Versus Saline in Intensive Care Study.

 Pragmatic, multicenter, 2x2 factorial randomized study.

 Severe patients admitted to the ICU at moderate to high risk for death or acute kidney injury will be randomly allocated to receive a balanced crystalloid solution (Plasma-Lyte(R)) or 0.

9% saline and to receive crystalloids by rapid bolus infusion (999 mL/h) or slow infusion (333 mL/h) whenever plasma expansion is needed.

